The paper discusses privacy and security issues in deep learning, which are typically addressed in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves combining feed-forward propagation and data encryption, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of localized first layer deep network also relates to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications in personal health-care, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
